parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the powertrain system can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
the "Gear Selected will Engage at Low Speed" message appears
the "D" indicator on the shift knob flashes
the vehicle decelerates to a low speed
and multiple warning lights and messages appear on the dashboard
including "Powertrain Malfunction"
"Reduced Power"
"Pre-Collision Assist Not Available"
"Hill Assist Not Available"
and "Service Engine Soon".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CV axle can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The CV axle fails
causing the vehicle to lose power and control
and may result in the parking brake engaging automatically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down completely, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
all warning lights and notices flash quickly
the vehicle dies
and the parking brake engages.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle entering limp mode and accelerating unintentionally can cause a loss of control, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle enters limp mode
flashes warning lights
and accelerates unintentionally
sometimes to high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with software updates can cause a range of problems, including electrical system failures, limp mode, and unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical system failures
enters limp mode
or accelerates unintentionally after a software update.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause a loss of control, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes fail to engage or disengage
causing the vehicle to slow down or speed up unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the battery and electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down or experience electrical system failures, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's battery drains quickly
the electrical system fails
or the vehicle enters "deep sleep" mode
causing electrical system failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Miscellaneous electrical issues can cause a range of problems, including electrical system failures, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical system failures
such as faulty turn signals
malfunctioning interior lights
or issues with the radio.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the regenerative braking system can cause the vehicle to stutter and jump while braking, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially in stop-and-go traffic. This can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes stutter and cause the vehicle to jump while braking
especially at low speeds; the brakes grab or apply suddenly
making it difficult to control the vehicle; the vehicle's brakes are unpredictable and inconsistent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to fail to stop immediately, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal is depressed
but the vehicle fails to stop immediately; the vehicle's brakes are slow to respond or fail to engage; the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake controller can cause the trailer brakes to fail to engage, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The brake controller does not activate the electric brakes on the trailer; the trailer brakes fail to engage or respond slowly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended braking can cause the vehicle to stop suddenly, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes engage suddenly without driver input; the vehicle's brakes apply suddenly
causing the vehicle to stop abruptly.
